post_text: Way to go Yearbook Students and Staff! Great job!
shared_text:
Keith N Cindy Abbott
May 8 at 3:42 PM ¬∑

I am soooo proud of my yearbook staff at Falls Lake Academy this year! Our publisher, Jostens, has awarded their yearbook, that THEY created, the National Yearbook Program of Excellence Award! I also want to mention my editor Kacey Katz, who led this staff as a sophomore (I've never had an editor that young, but she did great work!!), and Mrs. April Black our art and photography teacher who provided soooo much help! I'll never forget submitting the last few pages just minutes before our meeting where we were told schools were closing and we would be teaching online! Whew! We are the Firebirds, thus "The Flame"!

Falls Lake Academy Bands
March 2 at 11:34 AM ¬∑

‚Äî Pre-MPA HS Band Concert ‚Äî
As a reminder, our HS Symphonic Band will be having a short concert (which will serve as a pre-MPA performance) this Thursday night, on March 5th, in the HS Gym at 6:30.

We will be taking monetary Donations at the door to help the Band to buy new instruments or pay for the repairs of current instruments.

Also, we will be having a canned food drive. Our Band Concerts have always been free to the public, however we ask that your "price for attendance" be a donation of two canned goods. We will be donating all food to the local ACIM Food Bank.

post_text: Nearly every four years, we add an extra day to the calendar in the form of February 29, also known as Leap Day. Put simply, these additional 24 hours are built into the calendar to ensure that it stays in line with the Earth‚Äôs movement around the Sun.

üê∂ Carson Mendenhall's Senior Project üê∂

Carson Mendenhall is collecting t-shirts to make dog toys that will be sent to a local animal shelter. Her goal is to make enough toys so that every dog can have their own personal toy and can even take it with them to their forever home.

Please donate any old t-shirts or some you just don‚Äôt wear anymore! Donation boxes will be located in both the elementary/middle and high school buildings! Please feel free to contact Carson at carsonem01@gmail.com. Thank you for your help!

ATTENTION ALL ELEMENTARY AND MIDDLE SCHOOL PARENTS!

ü§ñü§ñü§ñ
Falls Lake Academy‚Äôs STEAM Club (Fire Hazard) is hosting several week-long robotics summer camps for rising 2-4 and rising 5-8 grade students using FIRST Lego WeDo and Mindstorms kits.

Campers will apply science, engineering, and math concepts, plus a big dose of imagination, to develop solutions to real-world challenges! If your student is interested in participating in one of these awesome camps, we plan on holding an interest meeting on March 5th at 4:00 pm in the library. We hope to see you all there!!

If there are any questions feel free to contact Gabe Bender at gabender24@gmail.com

TOMORROW, 2-6-2020, is the final day to sign up for our Annual Cheerleading Clinic on Saturday, February 15th from 11am-2pm. This is open to any student, grades K-7 who wants to learn how to become a cheerleader for the day.

This clinic will teach basic cheerleading skills such as motions, jumps, tumbling and even stunting! They will also be playing a few games. The cost is $50 per participant, which can be paid online through www.charterpay.org This cost includes a T-shirt and snack. If you have any further questions, please contact Miss Siegfried at amandasiegfried@fallslakeacademy.com

Please sign up at the link provided to reserve your spot today! Spaces are limited. forms.gle/wf9wRjPgvHqjJrzt8 We are very excited to teach our future Firebird athletes how to become a future Firebird Cheerleader! Thank you again for your continued support!

Miss Siegfried

üêùFalls Lake Academy's 2020 Spelling Bee will be coming up very soon!üêù

We are going to do the Spelling Bee a little differently this year. Students are being asked to volunteer if they would like to participate in the Spelling Bee.

If your student is interested in participating in the school Spelling Bee, please remind them to tell their PAA (grades 3-5) or their ELA teacher (grades 6-8).

The 3-5 Spelling Bee will be held on 2/12 at 6:30 p.m. The top speller in the 3-5 spelling bee will advance to our District Spelling Bee in March.

The 6-8 Spelling Bee will be held on 2/19 at 6:30 p.m.

Top spellers will also be recognized on Awards Day.

The Middle School Competition Cheerleading Squad will be hosting our Annual Cheerleading Clinic on Saturday, February 15th from 11am-2pm. This is open to any student, grades K-7 who wants to learn how to become a cheerleader for the day. This clinic will teach basic cheerleading skills such as motions, jumps, tumbling and even stunting! They will also playing a few games. The cost is $50 per participant, which can be paid online through www.charter pay.org. This cost includes a T-shirt and snack. The deadline for registration is Friday, February 7th. If you have any further questions, please contact Miss Siegfried at amandasiegfried@fallslakeacademy.com.

Please sign up at the link provided to reserve your spot today! Spaces are limited. https://forms.gle/wf9wRjPgvHqjJrzt8

We are very excited to teach our future Firebird athletes how to become a future Firebird Cheerleader!

Thank you again for your continued support,

Miss Siegfried

shared_text:
Falls Lake Academy Arts
December 9, 2019 at 5:50 PM ¬∑

About two years ago, as the crow flies, I inherited a DMV Waiting Room masquerading as an Art Classroom in a trailer with.... let's call it eccentric.... A/C-Heating unit.

Today, I have an ACTUAL Art Classroom, with adjustable drawing boards for every seat; 10 computers; 6 large light boxes; individual pro-level watercolor sets, for every seat; 9 gallons of tempera acrylic paint; 300 large sheets (can be halved) watercolor paper; Dozens of 8"x10" canvas boards; Dozens of 5"x7" canvas boards; Paint palettes with lids, enough for almost all three Middle School grades to have one per student, so they can keep and use for the year (tempera paint can be reactivated with water, so we have less waste); plus new brushes and other sundries.

A lot of time, effort, volunteering and fundraising has paid off.

To all who helped, volunteered, donated and supported the Arts Program at FLA, THIS is the results. Thank you all!

What next?

Polar Express Night this Friday!
At Barnes and Noble at Brier Creek on Friday, December 6th.
Come get some holiday shopping done and support FLA at this Firebird tradition.

Includes a nationwide Polar Express Night (wear your PJ's!) at 7p, a FLA Band concert in the store at 6p, and student art on display.

25% of purchases at B&N made comes back to the school! If you‚Äôve never come out, you should totally make it a night! It‚Äôs a lot of fun!

After Polar Express night, B&N will be providing mini-cups of hot cocoa and little sugar cookies for the little ones, a small craft, and a letter to Santa for them to fill in.

Friday night is also the Lighting of the Brier Creek Christmas Tree from 6-8p - featuring Santa, Carriage Rides, Trackless Train, Face Painters, DJ Daniel Jordan, and the Brier Creek Merchant Tree Decorating Competition.

*** Can‚Äôt make it? You can even shop online on Friday-Monday at BN.com - just make sure put in our Bookfair ID (12581328) when you are checking out.

post_text:
Care Packages for Our Troops

The FLA Color Guard will be collecting items to send to service members who will be serving our country overseas this holiday season.

We will be collecting items from Monday, November 18th through Friday, December 6th. There will be a collection box on each hall and in the front office.

Items that are needed are Good Socks, Toothbrushes, Toothpaste, Foot Powder, Sports Equipment, Wet Wipes, Deodorant, Beef Jerky, Hand Warmers, Playing Cards, Batteries, Puzzle Books, Protein Bars, Flavor Packets for Water, 3m Wall Hooks, Gum, Sunflower Seeds, Hot Sauce, and Palmers Hand Cream/Lotion.

If you have a family member serving overseas this holiday season please email their mailing info to Coach Porter at jasonporter@fallslakeacademy.com.

We would like to make sure that all service members with connections to FLA receive a care package.

Items that are needed are Good Socks, Toothbrushes, Toothpaste, Foot Powder, Sports Equipment, Wet Wipes, Deodorant, Beef Jerky, Hand Warmers, Playing Cards, Batteries, Puzzle Books, Protein Bars, Flavor Packets for Water, 3m Wall Hooks, Gum, Sunflower Seeds, Hot Sauce, and Palmers Hand Cream/Lotion.

If you have a family member serving overseas this holiday season please email their mailing info to Coach Porter at jasonporter@fallslakeacademy.com.

We would like to make sure that all service members with connections to FLA receive a care package.

FLA Arts Booster Club will be sponsoring 2 Halloween dances on Friday October 18th in the main gym. Elementary (3rd through 5th) will be from 315pm to 515 pm. Permission slips will be sent home this week and $5 must be turned in with the form prior to the dance. Middle School will be 630pm to 830pm with a $5 entry fee at the door. Pizza, snacks and drinks will be provided at both dances. Students may wear costumes at both dances, but must have appropriate shoes on, with no masks or weapons. Students from other schools are not allowed. Let us know if you have questions, sign up geniuses will be out in the next few days!
